item.dc:creator: @Natey Natey
item.description:
@Natey wrote:

[quote=“CoonHunter, post:18, topic:339784”][quote author=Natey link=topic=436159.msg3204318#msg3204318 date=1273637647]

[quote author=CoonHunter link=topic=436159.msg3204315#msg3204315 date=1273637523]

C++ is the best language IMO.
[/quote]atm I’m trying to learn basic java, just because it’s better for server, but then if I want to become a better server programmer I have a lot to learn about stuff for the actual server, like: protocols, what ISAAC (or whatever it is) means/does, etc.
So I have a long way to go

C++ is a great language, yes, but for something that anybody can do, I would say VB.net. VB.net is one of the easiest languages, while C++ is one of the harder ones. I personally do C# (C Sharp), since it provides some of the strengths of C++ but some of the friendly-ness that VB.net has. It also is easy to transfer from Java to C# as well, not in imports, but its alot of the same syntax, or at least what ive encoutered.
[/quote]Learning c++ made me want to commit suicide.
(bought a book with over 950+ pages D:)

Youtube

Thats how I figured out some very minor C++ things.[/quote]
